description:
Inari Ōkami, also called Ō-Inari (大稲荷)
One of the principal Kami (God) of Shinto, 
the Japanese kami of foxes with the blessing of general prosperity and worldly success

Omamori are Japanese amulets, used to ward off bad luck and evil, and thus for those who collect this I pray and wish for your health, success, and prosperity



digitally painted, part of VmachineZ collection 
depicting a scene of Inari Shinto shrine

3676 x 3676 pixel
